commitResults.messageTitle: Auto text ui testing for Level-4 regression testing

commitResults.messageBody:
Current code do not support persistent tasks.

Tasks are lost on exit of program.

Add file writing and reading to csv to export and import tasks.

CSV were chosen as it can be easily imported for other purposes.

CSV format:
Type,Completed,Task,By,From,To
0   ,1        ,2   ,3 ,4   ,5

Deadline was a String previously, giving no special meaning to it.

If deadline is a field that can capture date and have a temporal dimension we can do stuff related to time.
For example, we can give how much time remaining per task.

Change deadline from String to LocalDate
Add regex parsing instead
Update deadline saving and reading
Update Deadline creation command
Update help message

Event from and to was a String previously, giving no special meaning to it.

If from and to is a field that can capture date and have a temporal dimension we can do stuff related to time.
For example, we can give how much time remaining per task.

Change from, to from String to LocalDate
Add regex parsing to Event
Update Event saving and reading
Update Event creation command
Update help message for Event

commitResults.messageTitle: Add display for days remaining for Deadline and Event
commitResults.messageBody:
Current code have no additional utility that make use of the benefit of dates being stored as LocalDate instead of String

New addition allows days remaining to be calculated and displayed

Add days remaining or ago to Deadline and Event
Refactor Todo to use factories
Fix some alignment issues in Ui.shortSay
Rename some factory methods to be more clear or what they are used for
Update Todo to use Regex parsing

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix help message and indentation for command switch
Refactor the code to be more OOP by introducing Parser and Commands
commitResults.messageBody:
Currently, the code is one massive switch and cases inside Parser.

Update Commands enum to make use of some Functional Interfaces so Commands are functional interfaces and can be easily changed in their respective class.
